President Joe Biden has announced his intention to appoint four new members to the Commission on Fine Arts. The appointees are Peter Cook, a Principal at HGA Architects; Hazel Ruth Edwards, Professor and Chair at Howard University Department of Architecture; Justin Garrett Moore, Inaugural Program Officer at the Andrew Mellon Foundation; and Billie Tsien, Partner at Todd Williams Billie Tsien Architects. These individuals have impressive backgrounds in architecture, urban design, and academia, and their expertise will contribute to the commission's work in supporting non-profit, cultural, and academic institutions through enduring and meaningful architecture.